# Discord Bot Configuration
CLIENT_ID=your_client_id_here
PUBLIC_KEY=your_public_key_here
DISCORD_TOKEN=your_bot_token_here
BOT_TOKEN=your_bot_token_here
GUILD_ID=auto

# To manually set your GUILD_ID (optional):
# 1. Enable Developer Mode in Discord (User Settings > Advanced > Developer Mode)
# 2. Right-click your server name
# 3. Click "Copy Server ID"
# 4. Replace "auto" above with your server ID
# Example: GUILD_ID=123456789012345678

# How to get your values:
# 1. Go to https://discord.com/developers/applications
# 2. Create a new application or select existing one
# 3. Copy Application ID -> CLIENT_ID
# 4. Go to "Bot" section -> Copy Token -> DISCORD_TOKEN & BOT_TOKEN
# 5. Go to "General Information" -> Copy Public Key -> PUBLIC_KEY